title: US recently conducted cyber operation against Iran to protect election from foreign interference
description: The US National Security Agency and Cyber Command conducted an operation against Iran within the last two weeks as part of a broader effort to protect the 2020 election from foreign interference, a US official told CNN Tuesday.

title: We've been fighting over who gets to vote since 1787
description: The United States is a democracy, which means everyone gets to vote in US elections, right? Wrong. Who gets to vote and how easy it is for those voters to cast their ballots has been an ongoing fight since the U.S. Constitution was written.

description: John Legend took the stage at a rally for Democratic vice presidential nominee Sen. Kamala Harris Monday night and it was a family outing.

description: Numerous headstones at a Jewish cemetery in Grand Rapids, Michigan, were vandalized with "pro-Trump" messages, the Grand Rapids Police Department said Tuesday.

title: China pulls Ant Group's giant IPO after dust up with billionaire Jack Ma
description: Ant Group's highly anticipated IPO has been abruptly suspended following a meeting between the company's billionaire co-founder Jack Ma and regulators in China.

title: Disney's new robot has a creepily human gaze
description: Disney's new robot may be the stuff of nightmares, but it's actually supposed to look more lifelike and respond to human reactions.

title: Late-night hosts react to Trump potentially firing Dr. Fauci
description: Late-night hosts Jimmy Kimmel, Stephen Colbert, Jimmy Fallon, Seth Meyers, and James Corden are nervous for Election Day and give their take on the potential firing of Dr. Fauci.

title: Squads of both Ajax and Dynamo Kiev hit by multiple positive Covid-19 tests ahead of Champions League games
description: The squads of both Ajax and Dynamo Kyiv have been decimated by positive Covid-19 cases ahead of their respective Champions League matches.

title: Wales football manager Ryan Giggs arrested on suspicion of assault -- UK reports
description: The manager of the Welsh national football team and former Manchester United star Ryan Giggs has been arrested on suspicion of assault, British media reported Monday, and the Welsh Football Association said it was aware of an alleged incident without further comment, saying only that the 46-year-old would not be involved in upcoming matches.

title: Sri Lanka rescues 100 beached whales after mass stranding
description: Sri Lankan rescuers have returned 100 whales to sea after a mass beaching on Monday, the country's navy has said.

title: Bats can predict the future to hunt their prey, Johns Hopkins researchers find
description: Bats are often unfairly painted as blood-sucking vermin, but the researchers who study them would rather you think of them as the highly intelligent, largely benevolent creatures they are.

title: Three children pulled from rubble days after quake
description: More than 90 hours after a deadly earthquake struck Western Turkey, a 2-year-old girl was rescued from a collapsed building. A day earlier two other children were found alive. Rescue efforts to find survivors are ongoing.

title: Kris Jenner responds to Kendall party backlash
description: After Kendall Jenner was slammed for throwing a big 25th birthday bash on Halloween, her mother Kris Jenner said her family is "really responsible and we make sure that everyone in our family and our closest friends are tested religiously" for the coronavirus.

title: Twilight Payment wins Melbourne Cup in race marred by colt Anthony Van Dyck's fatal injury
description: Twilight Payment won the 2020 Melbourne Cup, Australia's most prestigious horse race, although the event was overshadowed by the death of Anthony Van Dyck, the Aidan O'Brien owned colt who broke down on the final straight at Flemington Racecourse.

title: How Wolf Blitzer and other news anchors are preparing for Election Day
description: Election Day is here, and news anchors are gearing up as Americans across the country prepare for the big night.

title: A young girl was shielded by a dishwasher after an earthquake and survived 91 hours trapped under rubble
description: A 2-year-old girl has been rescued from a collapsed building nearly 91 hours after a devastating earthquake hit the Aegean coastal Turkish city of Izmir on Friday.

title: Washington Post: Birx disputes Trump in calling for 'much more aggressive action' to combat pandemic
description: Dr. Deborah Birx sounded an alarming note about the state of the coronavirus in an internal White House report, saying the US is entering its "most deadly phase" yet, one that requires "much more aggressive action," according to The Washington Post.

title: Here's one way to predict who will win the Senate
description: Senate races across the country are converging with the trend in the presidential race in that same state, underscoring the increasingly parliamentary nature of American elections.

title: Bobi Wine, Ugandan singer and opposition presidential candidate, arrested
description: Ugandan opposition presidential candidate Bobi Wine was arrested on Tuesday after handing in his nomination papers to the election body, his party's spokesman said.

title: Thailand's online porn ban sparks backlash
description: Thailand's government said on Tuesday it had banned Pornhub and 190 other websites showing pornography, prompting social media anger over censorship and a protest against the decision.

title: Tom Brady reclaims NFL touchdown record in nail-biting victory over New York Giants
description: Tom Brady took on his familiar 'Comeback King' role last night as his Tampa Bay Buccaneers came from behind to narrowly defeat a feisty New York Giants team.

description: A passion for the sport won't be enough to power one through the ski season this year. Thanks to the pandemic, a successful 2020-21 ski season demands a flexible schedule, Type A-planning sensibilities and the financial means to do it all.

title: This entrepreneur helps Americans get Italian passports. Business has boomed during the pandemic

title: Watch small town cast first ballots on Election Day
description: Dixville Notch, New Hampshire, is one of three towns that usually votes at midnight on Election Day, but this year residents had to take extra precautions due to the Covid-19 pandemic.

title: Ex-GOP governor: I'm shocked by Rubio's remark at Trump rally
description: Former Republican governor of Ohio John Kasich and CNN's Don Lemon react to a comment by Senator Marco Rubio (R-FL) at a Trump rally where he referenced a caravan of Trump supporters who surrounded a Joe Biden campaign bus in what a Biden campaign official described as an attempt to run the bus off the road. The FBI is currently looking into the incident.

title: CNN panel gets heated over Trump's remarks on Pennsylvania
description: CNN's Anderson Cooper leads a panel discussion on President Trump's comments about the Supreme Court and voting in Pennsylvania.

title: This is CNN's final 2020 Electoral College outlook
description: Perhaps one of the most unexpected developments in the 2020 presidential campaign is how remarkably stable the state of the race has proved to be through extraordinarily turbulent times. As the race for the White House comes to a close, the landscape looks quite similar to how it looked after the party conventions in August as the fall campaign got underway.

title: Cooper: I never expected to last very long in this business
description: CNN's Anderson Cooper answers viewers' questions about his peculiar eating habits and what shaped his career path. Watch "Full Circle" every Monday, Tuesday and Friday at 6pm E.T.

title: See the fence being built around the White House
description: CNN's Alex Marquardt tours the "non-scalable" fence being built around the White House as the 2020 election looms.
